              <h1>Pension, Retirement and Estate Planning</h1>
<p><h4 >What is pension services?</h4>
<div>Pension may be described as regular payment which one aspires to receive regularly, once the person retires from his regular job or attain a certain age from which 
s/he does not want to work. It provides finalcial security and stabilty in the old age when people don't have a regular source of income. Pensions schemes give an 
oppurtunity to invest and accumulate savings and get lump sum amount income through annuity plans on retirement.</div></p>
<p><h4>National Pension System(NPS)</h4>
<div>NPS aims to institute pension reforms and to inculcate the habit of saving for retirement amonsgt the citizens. With effect from 1ST may 2009, nps has been provided for all
citizen among the country invluding the unorganised sector workers on voluntary basis. The subscriber will be alloted with a unique Permanent Retiremenr Account Number(PRAN) 
.This account no. with remain same for the rest of the life of the subscriber. This unique PRAN can be used from any location in India. NPS,indian govt. approved the age of indian citizen to 
be 18-65.</div></p>
<div>PRAN will provide access to two personal accounts -Tier I and Tier II with features as mentioned below:</div>
