<p><h4>Investment Options Under the NPS</h4>
<div>the subscribers to the NPS choose the investment options in which their contributions have to be invested.<br>
Following options are offered by the NPS.</div></p>
<div><p><b>E (Equity):</b>High Return, High Risk option-Fund invests predomaintly in equity-oriened investments.<br>
<b>C (Corporate Bonds):</b>Medium Return, Medium Rish option-Funds invests predomaintly in fixed income bearing securities other than govt. securities<br>
<b> G (Government Securities):</b>Low Return, Low Rish option-Fund investd predomaintly in pure low risk government fixed income securities.<br></p>
<p><b>Auto Choice Option:</b>The subscriber can choose the promotion of the funds that may be invested in each of the invested options.This is called a active  choise.The only restriction is the invested invested asset class E
cannot execeed 50% and that in asset A is restricted to 5%.<br>
<b>Auto Choise Option:</b>Under this choise the subscriber's contribution will be invested in the lifecycle fund.The lifecycle fund is dynamic allocation of the subscriber's wealth to different asset classes in a defines proportion 
determined by the age of the subscriber, with the exposure to equidity decrrasing and that to the safer corporate bonds.</p> </div>
