<p><h4>Retirement Planning</h4>
<div>The transtion into retirement is avery unique & dramamtic step in your life yet the transition into retirement is rarely given the planning or thougth . Every one wants to lead a easy retirement without plannnign it.</p>
<p>key features of retirement planning are:<br>
<b>1)Start Early and retire with financial security:</b>If yiu start saving for retirement at age of 25, so that you wish to retire by 60, you can invest over 35 years.<br>
<b>2)Plan wisely:</b>Set aside some money for medical expenditure at emergency needs after retirement.Allocate your savings toward important financial goals such as children's education and marriage.<br>
<b>3)Track and review your plan:</b>The financial plan has to be reviewed at regular intervals to make sure that the plan meeds its objective.Also you need to understand and get comfortable with cost and liquidity of your investment.<br></p></div>
<p><h4>ESTATE PLANNING</h4>
<div>Estate planning refers to planning during one's life time on making once assets to beneficial is typically family members loved ones ,So they can be created after once diminish with is and without any significant cost.Making a will is essential part of retirement planning</p></div>
<p><h4>WILL</h4>
<div>It is a written legal declaration of desires to distribute Assets of the decreased after his or her demise.This way one can transfer the assets to loved ones according to his or her preferences.
By making a will one can avoid any feud Among  beneficiaries over distribution of assets.</div></P>
<div><p>How to make a Will:<br>
<ul>
<li>Make a list of movable and immovable items</li>
<li>Decide which acid shall be given to whom (partially or fully)</li>
<li>Mention the name of the person and details who will execute the will</li>
<li>Get the will witnessed by a doctor and lawyer as it leads authenticity to the will</li>
<li>Registration of will is not compulsory</li>
<li>You may write the will on plain paper or take the help of a lawyer in making a will</li>
</ul></p>
<p>There are some problems that can arise in the absence of a will:<br>
<ul>
<li>Beneficiaries of the distribution of Assets and the quantum of benefits to them doesn't happen in way you would have liked</li>
<li>Asset distribution happens as per personal laws</li>
<li>May lead to expensive litigation among beneficiaries and other claimants</li>
<li>Succession disputes could take years to resolve and can be costly.Even in the absence of disputes the resolution process can be costly and reduce the benefits of asset inherited</li>
</ul></p></div>
<p><h4>Nomination</h4>
<div>Nominee is a person who receives the money on the death of the account holder.Nominee is only a custodian of the owner's money and does not have any ownership rights.
In the absence of nomination it could be expensive and time-consuming of all the legal Heirs of the decreased to get the money.is nomination mandatory in case of Demat account as well? Yes it elevates the problems faced by the legal Heirs in the case of a death of acc. holder.</div></p>


